* [[:en:Amaterasu|Amaterasu Ōmikami]] – A goddess born from Izanagi’s left eye (though some theories suggest she was originally a male deity<ref>Shōnensha, Gotō Zen, Watanabe Hiroyuki, Hanejōda Masahiko 『神道の本 八百万の神々がつどう秘教的祭祀の世界』 [[Gakken Holdings|Gakken]], pp.56-57.</ref>). She is the [[:en:Solar deity|Solar deity]]. * {{ill|Tsukuyomi-no-Mikoto|ja|月読命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsukuyomi-no-Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ツクヨミ}} – A deity born from Izanagi’s right eye. Although the text does not specify gender, he is generally considered a male deity. He governs the night as the [[:en:Lunar deity|Moon god]]. * [[:en:Susanoo-no-Mikoto|Susanoo-no-Mikoto]] – A male deity born from Izanagi’s nose. He is the {{ill|Sea deity|ja|海神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sea deity|qq=|1=water deity|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1916821}}, ruling over the oceans.
The ''[[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]]'' states in its main text that Izanagi and {{ill|Izanami|ja|伊邪那美|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izanami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to イザナミ|1=Izanami|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q682306}} declared, "How can we not give birth to the rulers of the heavens and earth?" and thus they begot four deities, among whom these three are included. Additionally, it notes that after the Moon God but before Susanoo, they also gave birth to {{ill|Hiruko|ja|ヒルコ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hiruko|qq=|1=Hiruko|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1067028}}.
